    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-02-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 11, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: Referring to the correspondence which
                            has taken place between us relative to the capture of the schooner Mount
                            Blanc, I now have the honor to enclose to you, for your information, the
                            copy of a letter, of the 2d instant, from the attorney of the United
                            States for the southern district of Florida, from which it will be seen
                            that that vessel has been restored to the master and claimant.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, your very obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
